sentences.english: Ripples undulating, that's damp thanksgiving of Ba River.
sentences.chinese: 涟漪泳动，那是巴河湿漉漉的感恩。

sentences.english: The granite pavement of the courtyard is wet because it rained last night.
sentences.chinese: 天井里的青石板是湿漉漉的，因为昨晚下了一阵雨。

sentences.english: He passed his hand across his forehead. It was dank with clammy sweat.
sentences.chinese: 他用手抹抹前额，额上满是湿漉漉粘糊糊的汗珠。

sentences.english: It began running down the wet valley.
sentences.chinese: 随后，它顺着湿漉漉的山谷奔跑起来。

sentences.english: Her hair was loose, and wet with snow and rain.
sentences.chinese: 她散乱的头发湿漉漉地沾满雨雪。

sentences.english: James came out of his bedroom, toweling his wet hair.
sentences.chinese: 詹姆斯从卧室出来，用毛巾擦着他湿漉漉的头发。

sentences.english: Apparition of these faces in the crowd. Petals on a wet, black, bough.
sentences.chinese: 人海中娇颜幽幽浮现，湿漉漉黑枝昙花片片。

sentences.english: The knife slipped from her wet hand and injured the pet beside her foot.
sentences.chinese: 刀从她湿漉漉的手中滑落，扎伤了她脚边的小宠物。

sentences.english: A feeling of wet struck on my face.
sentences.chinese: 我脸上有种湿漉漉的感觉。

sentences.english: Her hair was  loose, and wet with snow and rain.
sentences.chinese: 她散乱的头发湿漉漉地沾满雨雪。

sentences.english: Nobody could catch the wet ball, it was as slippery as an eel .
sentences.chinese: 谁也抓不住这个湿漉漉的球，它滑得像泥鳅。

sentences.english: The hay was blonde and damp and clung to their shoes.
sentences.chinese: 白花花的草湿漉漉地粘在鞋上。

sentences.english: He passed his hand across his forehead. it was dank with clammy sweat .
sentences.chinese: 他用手抹抹前额，额上满是湿漉漉粘糊糊的汗珠。

sentences.english: A waterlogged stick will do just fine.
sentences.chinese: 一根湿漉漉的竹棍就够了。

sentences.english: She trod casually, enjoying the touch of the damp grass on her feet.
sentences.chinese: 她信步而行，享受着湿漉漉的草地触及双脚的感觉。

sentences.english: Ruth held her close and stroked her wet forehead.
sentences.chinese: 鲁斯抱着女儿，抚摸着她湿漉漉的前额。

definition: to moisten/to dampen/to be steeped in/to be imbued with
muddy/covered in (mud, dust, sweat, blood etc)/daubed in
